import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Test {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer("aaa bbb ccceee fff ggg", " ");
        while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
            System.out.println(st.nextToken() + " 111");
        }
    }
}
<<<explanation>>>:
The StringTokenizer class is used to break a string into tokens.
The constructor of the StringTokenizer class takes two arguments:
1. The string to be tokenized.
2. The delimiter that separates the tokens.
The hasMoreTokens() method returns true if there are more tokens.
The nextToken() method returns the next token.
The code prints the tokens and adds "111" to the end of each token.
